  "body": "**Bug description:**\r\n\r\nWhen I run docker-compose I get this error:\r\n```\r\n(16/20) Installing pcre2 (10.36-r0)\r\n(17/20) Installing git (2.32.0-r0)\r\n(18/20) Installing linux-headers (5.10.41-r0)\r\n(19/20) Installing make (4.3-r0)\r\n(20/20) Installing musl-dev (1.2.2-r3)\r\nExecuting busybox-1.33.1-r2.trigger\r\nOK: 147 MiB in 35 packages\r\nRemoving intermediate container e1d81c36656f\r\n ---> cc5ad963dee7\r\nStep 3/10 : ADD ./l2geth /go-ethereum\r\n ---> 8df7636beeb5\r\nStep 4/10 : RUN cd /go-ethereum && make geth\r\n ---> Running in 4bf7f610711f\r\nenv GO111MODULE=on go run build/ci.go install ./cmd/geth\r\nmake: env: Operation not permitted\r\nmake: *** [Makefile:16: geth] Error 127\r\nERROR: Service 'l2geth' failed to build: The command '/bin/sh -c cd /go-ethereum && make geth' returned a non-zero code: 2\r\n```\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce**\r\nThe exact steps are documented in https://github.com/qbzzt/optimism-tutorial/blob/main/README.md. You create a Debian 10 VM on GCP (it fails even with a 16 GB one), and then execute:\r\n```\r\nsudo apt install -y wget git docker docker.io build-essential docker-compose\r\ncurl -sL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_12.x -o nodesource_setup.sh\r\nsudo bash nodesource_setup.sh\r\nsudo apt install -y nodejs\r\nsudo npm install -g yarn hardhat\r\nsudo usermod -a -G docker `whoami`\r\n```\r\n\r\nThen open a new command line and run:\r\n```\r\ngit clone https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism.git\r\ncd optimism\r\nyarn install\r\nyarn build\r\ncd ops\r\ndocker-compose build\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nI expected `docker-compose` to create for me a working Optimism setup I can use to test things out.\r\n\r\n**System Specs:**\r\n - OS: Debian 10\r\n - Package Version (or commit hash): Latest\r\n",
